{"result":[{"short_description":"Quick Filters","sys_mod_count":"7","sys_updated_on":"2015-01-06 20:10:38","sys_tags":"","sys_class_name":"cool_thing","number":"COOL0000005","sys_id":"133d8aa95f101100a9ad2572f2b47725","sys_package":{"link":"https://dev315171.service-now.com/api/now/v1/table/sys_package/e08b63f304352210559073c06a02f7e8","value":"e08b63f304352210559073c06a02f7e8"},"sys_update_name":"cool_thing_133d8aa95f101100a9ad2572f2b47725","sys_updated_by":"admin","sys_created_on":"2013-10-08 17:19:42","sys_name":"COOL0000005","sys_scope":{"link":"https://dev315171.service-now.com/api/now/v1/table/sys_scope/global","value":"global"},"text":"<div style=\"font-size: 2em;\">Quick Filters</div>\n<hr />\n<table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\">\n<p>How about a third easy way to distill your data, using a filter to see all Priority 1 <i>and</i> 2 Incidents? Navigate back to <b>Incident</b> &gt; <b>All</b>. Click the filter toggle next to the list breadcrumbs to expand the current filter conditions (there aren&#39;t any).</p>\n<p>Where you see &#34;-- choose field --&#34;, set the following condition: Field &#61; &#34;Priority&#34;; Operator &#61; &#34;is one of&#34;; Values &#61; both &#34;1 - Critical&#34; <em>and</em> &#34;2 - High&#34; (hold down the <em>Ctrl </em>key on the keyboard to select multiple values).</p>\n<p>Click <b>Run</b> when finished. The result is a filtered list of all Priority 1 and 2 Incidents. To save this filter so you could quickly run it anytime, you would have clicked &#34;Save...&#34;, given the filter a name, set the visibility, and clicked <b>Save</b>.</p>\n</td><td style=\"width: 10px;\"> </td><td><img style=\"align: baseline;\" title=\"\" src=\"/10Things05a_v2.pngx\" alt=\"\" align=\"baseline\" border=\"\" hspace=\"\" vspace=\"\" /></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p> </p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"> </p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\" width=\"45%\">Previous: <a style=\"color: #6ab7ef