5</a></li><li><a title=\"Unload Data in a Form You Can Use\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000006\" rel=\"nofollow\">6</a></li><li><a title=\"Natural Language Searching\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000007\" rel=\"nofollow\">7</a></li><li><a title=\"Configure a Form\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000008\" rel=\"nofollow\">8</a></li><li><a title=\"View Reports\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000009\" rel=\"nofollow\">9</a></li><li><a title=\"Create a Report\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000010\" rel=\"nofollow\">10</a></li></ul>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p> </p>","sys_created_by":"glide.james","sys_policy":""},{"short_description":"Natural Language Searching","sys_mod_count":"8","sys_updated_on":"2015-01-06 20:13:51","sys_tags":"","sys_class_name":"cool_thing","number":"COOL0000007","sys_id":"3b5d8aa95f101100a9ad2572f2b4772e","sys_package":{"link":"https://dev315171.service-now.com/api/now/v1/table/sys_package/e08b63f304352210559073c06a02f7e8","value":"e08b63f304352210559073c06a02f7e8"},"sys_update_name":"cool_thing_3b5d8aa95f101100a9ad2572f2b4772e","sys_updated_by":"admin","sys_created_on":"2013-10-08 17:20:17","sys_name":"COOL0000007","sys_scope":{"link":"https://dev315171.service-now.com/api/now/v1/table/sys_scope/global","value":"global"},"text":"<div style=\"font-size: 2em;\">Natural Language Searching</div>\n<hr />\n<p>In ServiceNow, you can easily search for specific text across most fields. Navigate back to <b>Incident</b><span> &gt; </span><b>All</b><span> and Search &#34;for text&#34;.</span></p>\n<p>Type &#34;network&#34; in the search box, and hit [Enter] to see the results. ServiceNow returned all records containing the word &#34;network&#34;, regardless of where that text actually appeared. You don&#39;t need to specify which field to search. You don&#39;t even have to know which fields are available.</p>\n<table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td><img style=\"align: baseline;\" title=\"\" src=\"/10Things07a_v2.pngx\" alt=\"\" align=\"baseline\" border=\"\" hspace=\"\" vspace=\"\" /></td><td> </td><td><span style=\"color: #6699cc; font-size: large;\" color=\"#6699cc\" size=\"4\"> </span></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p> </p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"> </p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\" width=\"45%\">Previous: <a style=\"color: #6ab7ef;\" title=\"Unload Data\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000006\" rel=\"nofollow\">Unload Data</a><br />Next: <a style=\"color: #6ab7ef;\" title=\"Configure a Form\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000008\" rel=\"nofollow\">Configure a Form</a></td><td align=\"right\">\n<ul class=\"pagination\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\"><li><a title=\"Ten Things\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do\" rel=\"nofollow\">&lt;&lt;</a></li><li><a title=\"Right-click Charting\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000001\" rel=\"nofollow\">1</a></li><li><a title=\"Use a Chart to Filter Data\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000002\" rel=\"nofollow\">2</a></li><li><a title=\"Right-click filtering\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000003\" rel=\"nofollow\">3</a></li><li><a title=\"One Click Sorting\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000004\" rel=\"nofollow\">4</a></li><li><a title=\"Quick Filters\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000005\" rel=\"nofollow\">5</a></li><li><a title=\"Unload Data in a Form You Can Use\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000006\" rel=\"nofollow\">6</a></li><li class=\"active\"><a title=\"Natural Language Searching\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000007\" rel=\"nofollow\">7</a></li><li><a title=\"Configure a Form\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000008\" rel=\"nofollow\">8</a></li><li><a title=\"View Reports\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000009\" rel=\"nofollow\">9</a></li><li><a title=\"Create a Report\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000010\" rel=\"nofollow\">10</a></li></ul>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p> </p>","sys_created_by":"glide.james","sys_policy":""},{"short_description":"Use a Chart to Filter Data","sys_mod_count":"10","sys_updated_on":"2015-01-06 20:05:15","sys_tags":"","sys_class_name":"cool_thing","number":"COOL0000002","sys_id":"4d0d0aa95f101100a9ad2572f2b47761","sys_package":{"link":"https://dev315171.service-now.com/api/now/v1/table/sys_package/e08b63f304352210559073c06a02f7e8","value":"e08b63f304352210559073c06a02f7e8"},"sys_update_name":"cool_thing_4d0d0aa95f101100a9ad2572f2b47761","sys_updated_by":"admin","sys_created_on":"2013-10-08 17:18:50","sys_name":"COOL0000002","sys_scope":{"link":"https://dev315171.service-now.com/api/now/v1/table/sys_scope/global","value":"global"},"text":"<div style=\"font-size: 2em;\">Use a Chart to Filter Data</div>\n<hr />\n<p><span>Since we&#39;re looking at the pie chart we just made, let&#39;s see what we can do with it. What if we&#39;re interested in seeing just the high priority Incidents? Easier done than said. Just click the pie wedge representing those Incidents - in this case, the green wedge.</span></p>\n<p><span>Once you click through, you&#39;ll see a list of the Incidents represented by the pie wedge you clicked. The same &#34;click through&#34; action works with bar charts.</span></p>\n<table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td><img style=\"align: baseline;\" title=\"\" src=\"/10Things02a_v2.pngx\" alt=\"\" align=\"baseline\" border=\"\" hspace=\"\" vspace=\"\" /></td><td> </td><td><span style=\"color: #6699cc; font-size: large;\" color=\"#6699cc\" size=\"4\"> </span></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p> </p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"> </p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\" width=\"45%\">Previous: <a style=\"color: #6ab7ef;\" title=\"Right-click Charting\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000001\" rel=\"nofollow\">Right-click Charting</a><br />Next: <a style=\"color: #6ab7ef;\" title=\"Right-click Filtering\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000003\" rel=\"nofollow\">Right-click Filtering</a></td><td align=\"right\">\n<ul class=\"pagination\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\"><li><a title=\"Ten Things\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do\" rel=\"nofollow\">&lt;&lt;</a></li><li><a title=\"Right-click Charting\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000001\" rel=\"nofollow\">1</a></li><li class=\"active\"><a title=\"Use a Chart to Filter Data\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000002\" rel=\"nofollow\">2</a></li><li><a title=\"Right-click filtering\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000003\" rel=\"nofollow\">3</a></li><li><a title=\"One Click Sorting\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000004\" rel=\"nofollow\">4</a></li><li><a title=\"Quick Filters\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000005\" rel=\"nofollow\">5</a></li><li><a title=\"Unload Data in a Form You Can Use\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000006\" rel=\"nofollow\">6</a></li><li><a title=\"Natural Language Searching\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000007\" rel=\"nofollow\">7</a></li><li><a title=\"Configure a Form\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000008\" rel=\"nofollow\">8</a></li><li><a title=\"View Reports\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000009\" rel=\"nofollow\">9</a></li><li><a title=\"Create a Report\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000010\" rel=\"nofollow\">10</a></li></ul>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p> </p>","sys_created_by":"glide.james","sys_policy":""},{"short_description":"Create a Report","sys_mod_count":"9","sys_updated_on":"2015-01-06 23:21:50","sys_tags":"","sys_class_name":"cool_thing","number":"COOL0000010","sys_id":"5f9dc2695f101100a9ad2572f2b477e2","sys_package":{"link":"https://dev315171.service-now.com/api/now/v1/table/sys_package/e08b63f304352210559073c06a02f7e8","value":"e08b63f304352210559073c06a02f7e8"},"sys_update_name":"cool_thing_5f9dc2695f101100a9ad2572f2b477e2","sys_updated_by":"admin","sys_created_on":"2013-10-08 17:21:23","sys_name":"COOL0000010","sys_scope":{"link":"https://dev315171.service-now.com/api/now/v1/table/sys_scope/global","value":"global"},"text":"<div style=\"font-size: 2em;\">Create a Report</div>\n<hr />\n<table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\">\n<p>ServiceNow provides many intuitive reports, but creating your own is easier than you think. Let&#39;s create a report that groups all open Incidents by assignment group, stacked by priority. This will tell us which groups are dealing with the high priority issues.</p>\n<p>Navigate back to <b>Reports</b> &gt; <b>View / Run</b> and click the <strong>Create a report</strong> button to open the report builder. Change the <b>Table</b> to &#34;Incident&#34;, the Type to &#34;Bar&#34;, the <b>Group by</b> field to &#34;Assignment group&#34;, and the <b>Stacked by </b>field to &#34;Priority&#34;. Click the <strong>Run </strong>button to see the results.</p>\n<p><span>The report immediately tells us that there are five critical Incidents that haven&#39;t been assigned to a group yet - definitely something to fix quickly! And creating this report from scratch took less than a minute. To save even more time running this report in the future, give it a name and click </span><strong>Save</strong><span>. Now when you go </span><span>to </span><b>Reports</b><span> &gt; </span><b>View / Run</b><span>, your new report will be there. If you made it globally available before saving it, everyone in your organization will be able to run it.</span></p>\n</td><td style=\"width: 10px;\"> </td><td><img style=\"align: baseline;\" title=\"\" src=\"/10Things10a_v2.pngx\" alt=\"\" align=\"baseline\" border=\"\" hspace=\"\" vspace=\"\" /> </td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p> </p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"font-size: