v style=\"font-size: 2em;\">Right-click Filtering</div>\n<hr />\n<p><span>Now that we&#39;ve looked at using charts to filter data, let&#39;s try an even easier way to get that same list of high priority Incidents. </span>Navigate<span> back to </span><b>Incident</b><span> &gt; </span><b>All</b><span> to see the complete list of Incidents. Right-click on a Priority 2 Incident&#39;s <strong>Priority</strong> value, and select &#34;Show Matching&#34;.</span></p>\n<p><span>Voila! Conversely, you could have viewed everything </span><i>except</i><span> Priority 2 Incidents by selecting &#34;Filter Out&#34; instead.</span></p>\n<table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td><img style=\"align: baseline;\" title=\"\" src=\"/10Things03a_v2.pngx\" alt=\"\" align=\"baseline\" border=\"\" hspace=\"\" vspace=\"\" /></td><td> </td><td><span style=\"color: #6699cc; font-size: large;\" color=\"#6699cc\" size=\"4\"> </span></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p> </p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"> </p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\" width=\"45%\">Previous: <a style=\"color: #6ab7ef;\" title=\"Use a Chart to Filter Data\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000002\" rel=\"nofollow\">Use a Chart to Filter Data</a><br />Next: <a style=\"color: #6ab7ef;\" title=\"One-click Sorting\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000004\" rel=\"nofollow\">One-click Sorting</a></td><td align=\"right\">\n<ul class=\"pagination\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\"><li><a title=\"Ten Things\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do\" rel=\"nofollow\">&lt;&lt;</a></li><li><a title=\"Right-click Charting\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000001\" rel=\"nofollow\">1</a></li><li><a title=\"Use a Chart to Filter Data\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000002\" rel=\"nofollow\">2</a></li><li class=\"active\"><a title=\"Right-click filtering\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000003\" rel=\"nofollow\">3</a></li><li><a title=\"One Click Sorting\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000004\" rel=\"nofollow\">4</a></li><li><a title=\"Quick Filters\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000005\" rel=\"nofollow\">5</a></li><li><a title=\"Unload Data in a Form You Can Use\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000006\" rel=\"nofollow\">6</a></li><li><a title=\"Natural Language Searching\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000007\" rel=\"nofollow\">7</a></li><li><a title=\"Configure a Form\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000008\" rel=\"nofollow\">8</a></li><li><a title=\"View Reports\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000009\" rel=\"nofollow\">9</a></li><li><a title=\"Create a Report\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000010\" rel=\"nofollow\">10</a></li></ul>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p> </p>","sys_created_by":"glide.james","sys_policy":""},{"short_description":"Unload Data in a Form You Can Use","sys_mod_count":"7","sys_updated_on":"2015-01-06 20:12:03","sys_tags":"","sys_class_name":"cool_thing","number":"COOL0000006","sys_id":"a74d8aa95f101100a9ad2572f2b4771e","sys_package":{"link":"https://dev315171.service-now.com/api/now/v1/table/sys_package/e08b63f304352210559073c06a02f7e8","value":"e08b63f304352210559073c06a02f7e8"},"sys_update_name":"cool_thing_a74d8aa95f101100a9ad2572f2b4771e","sys_updated_by":"admin","sys_created_on":"2013-10-08 17:19:59","sys_name":"COOL0000006","sys_scope":{"link":"https://dev315171.service-now.com/api/now/v1/table/sys_scope/global","value":"global"},"text":"<div style=\"font-size: 2em;\">Unload Data in a Form You Can Use</div>\n<hr />\n<table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\">\n<p>You&#39;ve seen how ServiceNow can show you just the information you need. Now we&#39;ll show you ways to convert that information to other useful formats. We&#39;ll continue to use Incidents for this example, so navigate back to <b>Incident</b> &gt; <b>All</b>.</p>\n<p><span>This time, right-click anywhere in the list header. You&#39;ll see four &#34;Export&#34; options: Excel, CSV, XML and PDF. Selecting any of these will convert the list into the chosen format. Depending on your browser, you&#39;ll then be prompted to either save or open the resultant file. The best thing is that all this takes less time than it probably just took you to read this paragraph.</span></p>\n</td><td style=\"width: 10px;\"> </td><td><img style=\"align: baseline;\" title=\"\" src=\"/10Things06a_v2.pngx\" alt=\"\" align=\"baseline\" border=\"\" hspace=\"\" vspace=\"\" /></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p> </p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\" width=\"45%\">Previous: <a style=\"color: #6ab7ef;\" title=\"Quick Filters\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000005\" rel=\"nofollow\">Quick Filters</a><br />Next: <a style=\"color: #6ab7ef;\" title=\"Natural Language Searching\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000007\" rel=\"nofollow\">Natural Language Searching</a></td><td align=\"right\">\n<ul class=\"pagination\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\"><li><a title=\"Ten Things\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do\" rel=\"nofollow\">&lt;&lt;</a></li><li><a title=\"Right-click Charting\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000001\" rel=\"nofollow\">1</a></li><li><a title=\"Use a Chart to Filter Data\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000002\" rel=\"nofollow\">2</a></li><li><a title=\"Right-click filtering\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000003\" rel=\"nofollow\">3</a></li><li><a title=\"One Click Sorting\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000004\" rel=\"nofollow\">4</a></li><li><a title=\"Quick Filters\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000005\" rel=\"nofollow\">5</a></li><li class=\"active\"><a title=\"Unload Data in a Form You Can Use\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000006\" rel=\"nofollow\">6</a></li><li><a title=\"Natural Language Searching\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000007\" rel=\"nofollow\">7</a></li><li><a title=\"Configure a Form\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000008\" rel=\"nofollow\">8</a></li><li><a title=\"View Reports\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000009\" rel=\"nofollow\">9</a></li><li><a title=\"Create a Report\" href=\"/10_cool_things.do?sysparm_page&#61;COOL0000010\" rel=\"nofollow\">10</a></li></ul>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p> </p>\n<div id=\"mceResizeHandlen\" class=\"mce-resizehandle\" style=\"cursor: n-resize; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; left: 330.5px; top: 50.8125px; display: block;\"></div>\n<div id=\"mceResizeHandlee\" class=\"mce-resizehandle\" style=\"cursor: e-resize; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; left: 656.5px; top: 243.8125px; display: block;\"></div>\n<div id=\"mceResizeHandles\" class=\"mce-resizehandle\" style=\"cursor: s-resize; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; left: 330.5px; top: 436.8125px; display: block;\"></div>\n<div id=\"mceResizeHandlew\" class=\"mce-resizehandle\" style=\"cursor: w-resize; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; left: 4.5px; top: 243.8125px; display: block;\"></div>\n<div id=\"mceResizeHandlenw\" class=\"mce-resizehandle\" style=\"cursor: nw-resize; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; left: 4.5px; top: 50.8125px; display: block;\"></div>\n<div id=\"mceResizeHandlene\" class=\"mce-resizehandle\" style=\"cursor: ne-resize; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; left: 656.5px; top: 50.8125px; display: block;\"></div>\n<div id=\"mceResizeHandlese\" class=\"mce-resizehandle\" style=\"cursor: se-resize; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; left: 656.5px; top: 436.8125px; display: block;\"></div>\n<div id=\"mceResizeHandlesw\" class=\"mce-resizehandle\" style=\"cursor: sw-resize; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; left: 4.5px; top: 436.8125px; display: block;\"></div>","sys_created_by":"glide.james","sys_policy":""},{"short_description":"Configure a Form","sys_mod_count":"11","sys_updated_on":"2015-01-06 20:15:40","sys_tags":"","sys_class_name":"cool_thing","number":"COOL0000008","sys_id":"a87d8aa95f101100a9ad2572f2b47759","sys_package":{"link":"https://dev315171.service-now.com/api/now/v1/table/sys_package/e08b63f304352210559073c06a02f7e8","value":"e08b63f304352210559073c06a02f7e8"},"sys_update_name":"cool_thing_a87d8aa95f101100a9ad2572f2b47759","sys_updated_by":"admin","sys_created_on":"2013-10-08 17:20:45","sys_name":"COOL0000008","sys_scope":{"link":"https://dev315171.service-now.com/api/now/v1/table/sys_scope/global","value":"global"},"text":"<div style=\"font-size: 2em;\">Configure a Form</div>\n<hr />\n<p><span>At ServiceNow, we design our forms to be clear and concise. We try to include the fields you need and </span><i>only</i><span> the fields you need. We realize, however, that every organization is unique*. With that in mind, we make it easy to configure forms.</span></p>\n<p>To see how, navigate to <b>User Administration</b> &gt; <b>Users</b>, and click <strong>New</strong>. You&#39;ll see an empty &#34;User&#34; form, ready for input. Say, for example, your organization decides it doesn&#39;t want to use photos in the user records. In that case, it would make sense to remove that field from the form.</p>\n<p>To configure any form, right-click the form header and select <strong>Configure &gt; Form Design</strong>. <span>On the left you&#39;ll see a list of available fields, while on the right you&#39;ll see the layout of what is currently on the form. You can drag and drop to add/remove fields or move them around. You can even create new fields right here. Click <strong>Save</strong></span><span><strong> </strong>when done.</span></p>\n<table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\">\n<p><img style=\"align: baseline;\" title=\"\" src=\"/10Things08a_v2.pngx\" alt=\"\" align=\"baseline\" border=\"\" hspace=\"\" vspace=\"\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>* <span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">except the one that isn&#39;t...</span></p>\n</td><td style=\"width: 100%;\"> </td><td><img style=\"align: 